<br>
I took my cleric and mage into the Arena (remember that place, the one in Lake Rathe?  hehe) and did some testing with pets and their DDs.<br>
<br>
There's a PVP nerf of course.  Char (at 54) was doing 428 max dmg.  The pets did as follows spell-wise<br>
<br>
51 Earth - 55 DD w/ Root<br>
52 Fire - 110 Fire DD, 148 (149?) Fire DD and 179(178?) Magic DD<br>
53 Air - 55 DD w/ Stun<br>
54 Water - 110 DD<br>
<br>
I then gave my pet Opal Bracelet and saw no difference in DD.  Same with Ruby.  <br>
<br>
I then timed the casting times for the spells on the fire pet and gave him a Twisted ring and Studded ring and noticed no difference in cast times.<br>
<br>
So my assumption here is that pets cannot benefit from the focus items we make, except for the hps and what not, since the time reducing ring did not make a difference.<br>
<br>
Also, are these DD casts nerfed the same as PC spells in PVP or is this what they actually do dmg wise?<br>
<br>
I am going to try to test this out with this information vs some low level mobs that can stand a few blasts from the pets DDs.<br>
<br>
I figure if I cast Char without focus items, note the percent of damage it does, then have the pet attack/backoff a rooted mob, I should be able to calculate the DD done after a couple fights.<br>
<br>
If anyone knows the answer though, I'll skip that and just read the forum =)<br>
<br>
BTW i'm pulling with malosi so they should be hitting for max DD every time on a mob that is lower level than them.<br>
<br>
Wrathen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 8:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Equipping pets</span><hr size=1> Apparently the &quot;spells&quot; that our pets is casting are skill based rather than spell based. That's how pet can keep on casting without running out of mana. The only bottle neck is the recycle time (recast time) of the spells. This system works very much like Paladin's LoH. The focus items only works on &quot;true&quot; spells not skill based spells.  <p><p><a
