src="http://www.animearki.com/anniemei/alladdim.jpg" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 4:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Answers...</span><hr size=1> Indeed<br>
<br>
The pets do the same damage (51-54 pets) in PVP as they do vs mobs for their DD spells.  I tested with the water pet (only 1 was needed).<br>
<br>
I rooted giants with a cleric and chain cast root while I nuked with sigil (450) with the mage.  Pulled with malosi so that the max damage would be easier to pull off (no resists on pet hehe).<br>
<br>
It only took 1 giant to confirm but I did 10 anyways.  I would nuke twice (seeing the percent droppage on each nuke) then /pet attack, /pet back off over and over and watched how much the pet nuked.<br>
<br>
Tests show an average of 106 dmg by the water pet's DD spell.  I did the following math on giants with approx 5300 hps:<br>
<br>
450 nuke dropped the giant 8% the first cast and 9% more on the next.  Both hit for 450 so I'm assuming it really did 8.5% on both.  <br>
so 100%/ 8.5% = 11.8(about)<br>
11.8* 450 = 5310 (thus how i figured out how many hps the mob had)<br>
The water pet did about 2% damage each cast<br>
5310 * .02 = 106<br>
<br>
Thats pretty darn identical to the 110 it does vs players so I am going to leap here and say its the same.<br>
<br>
So it would point to pets' DD spells being considered a 'skill' instead of a spell.  Therefore, summoned focus items did not make a difference (as alladdim stated).<br>
<br>
So if you want to know how much DD your pet does, drag a friend to the arena and see what they hit for with malosi on =)<br>
<br>
<br>
Wrathen<br>
